<li sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="84">In the navigation pane, go to <strong sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="84">Modules &gt; Credit and collections &gt; Periodic tasks &gt; Age customer balances</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<ul sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="85">
<li sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="85">Select an aging period definition. The aging snapshot process ages transactions according to the aging periods that are defined in the selected aging period definition.</li>
<li sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="86">Select a customer pool or leave this field blank to create an aging snapshot for all customers. If a customer pool is selected, the aging snapshot process is applied only to the customer accounts that are part of the customer pool. The selected customer pool must be of the Aging snapshot type.</li>
<li sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="87">Select the type of date to base the aging snapshot on.
<ul sourcefile="finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/review-collections-information.md" sourcestartlinenumber="88">
